{"questionId": "cbc4c163", "correctAnswer": "11/4", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Substitute", "content": "Plug $x=\\tfrac{1}{4}$ into $f(x)=5\\left(\\tfrac{1}{4}-x\\right)^{2}+\\tfrac{11}{4}$.<br/>$$f\\!\\left(\\tfrac{1}{4}\\right)=5\\left(\\tfrac{1}{4}-\\tfrac{1}{4}\\right)^{2}+\\tfrac{11}{4}$$"}, {"title": "Compute the result", "content": "The squared term is $0$.<br/>$$f\\!\\left(\\tfrac{1}{4}\\right)=5(0)+\\tfrac{11}{4}=\\tfrac{11}{4}$$<br/>The answer is <strong>11/4</strong>.", "desmosExpressions": ["f(x)=5(((1)/(4)-x))^(2)+(11)/(4)"]}]}
